#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Visão geral"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"When you run a Quarkus application in dev mode, you can expose a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server.\n"
"It presents the methods used by the DevUI *MCP tools* (methods you can call) and the data exposed by *MCP resources*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Connecting an MCP client"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"Open the **Dev UI** settings dialog and select the Dev MCP tab.\n"
"There you can enable Dev MCP, get the connection details (Default `http://localhost:8080/q/dev-mcp`) and see what clients are connected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"Any MCP client that supports the https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-03-26[Streamable Protocol, version 2025‑03‑26] can connect using that URL.\n"
"After a client connects, it will appears on the tab:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Guide for extension developers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"Extensions can contribute additional tools and resources to the Dev MCP server. The integration is similar to contributing to the xref:dev-ui.adoc[Dev UI], but descriptions are mandatory.\n"
"A single JSON‑RPC service can be used for both Dev UI and Dev MCP; methods without a description only show up in Dev UI, while methods with a description appear in both."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Extension skills"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Extensions can ship a `quarkus-skill.md` file to provide AI coding agents with extension-specific coding guidelines, testing patterns, and common pitfalls. During the Quarkus build, all skill files are automatically discovered, composed with extension metadata (name, description, guide URL, categories), and aggregated into a single `io.quarkus:quarkus-extension-skills` JAR following the https://agentskills.io/specification[Agent Skills specification]. This JAR is published to Maven Central with each Quarkus release and is compatible with https://www.skillsjars.com[SkillsJars]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Adding a skill file to your extension"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Place a `quarkus-skill.md` file in your extension's deployment module at:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "That's it. No pom.xml changes are needed. The Quarkus build automatically discovers all `quarkus-skill.md` files across all extensions and aggregates them into the `quarkus-extension-skills` artifact."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "If your extension's runtime module has a `description` field in `META-INF/quarkus-extension.yaml`, it will be included in the composed skill's YAML frontmatter to help AI agents discover and understand your extension. The `categories` field under `metadata` is also included, allowing AI agents to group skills by category. While optional, providing a description and categories is recommended:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The file should contain concise, actionable Markdown content. Focus on what an AI agent needs to know to use your extension correctly:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Key patterns** — how to use the main APIs, annotations, and CDI beans."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Testing** — how to write tests using `@QuarkusTest`, Dev Services, and extension-specific test utilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Common pitfalls** — mistakes that agents (and developers) frequently make."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Example for a hypothetical extension:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "What gets composed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The skill file content is **not** shipped as-is. During the Quarkus build, the `aggregate-skills` goal scans the source tree for all `quarkus-skill.md` files and composes each one with extension metadata to produce a `SKILL.md` file at `META-INF/skills/{extension-name}/SKILL.md` inside the aggregated JAR. The composed document follows the https://agentskills.io/specification[Agent Skills specification] and includes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**YAML frontmatter** — the skill name, extension description from `quarkus-extension.yaml`, license, guide URL, and categories as structured metadata for agent discovery."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Skill body** — the patterns, testing guidelines, and pitfalls authored by the extension developer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Dev MCP tools** — the skill is automatically enriched with an \"Available Dev MCP Tools\" section listing each MCP tool the extension enables by default, including tool names, descriptions, and parameters. Tools are discovered from runtime methods annotated with both `@JsonRpcDescription` and `@DevMCPEnableByDefault`, and from deployment processor classes annotated with `@DevMcpBuildTimeTool`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Example of a composed `SKILL.md`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The Dev MCP tools section is appended during the Quarkus build by the `aggregate-skills` Maven goal. Only tools that are enabled by default are included. All modules are scanned via Jandex on compiled classes. The enriched skills are baked into the `quarkus-extension-skills` JAR published with each Quarkus release."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "For **runtime methods**, add both `@JsonRpcDescription` and `@DevMCPEnableByDefault` annotations on the method (see <<MCP Tools against the Runtime classpath>>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "For **deployment build-time actions**, annotate the processor class with `@DevMcpBuildTimeTool`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The tool name, matching the `methodName` in the builder chain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "A human-readable description of what this tool does."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Parameter descriptions. Use `required = false` for optional parameters."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The annotation is repeatable — add one per tool on the same class. This is the deployment-classpath counterpart of `@JsonRpcDescription` + `@DevMCPEnableByDefault` used on runtime methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "What NOT to put in the skill file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Extension description or guide links** — these are automatically added from `quarkus-extension.yaml`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Configuration properties** — reference the guide instead. A link is auto-generated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "**Obvious instructions** — focus on Quarkus-specific patterns and gotchas, not generic advice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "MCP tools"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"A tool corresponds to a method that a client can call. Any JSON‑RPC method can be exposed as a tool by supplying descriptions on the method and its parameters.\n"
"Tools can run on either the runtime or deployment classpath."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "MCP Tools against the Runtime classpath"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "To expose runtime information or actions (for example, changing log levels), define a xref:dev-ui.adoc#jsonrpc-against-the-runtime-classpath[JSON‑RPC service] in your runtime or runtime‑dev module and annotate the methods and parameters with `@JsonRpcDescription`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Description of the method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Description of each parameter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "By default this tool will be disabled, and the user has to enable it in Dev UI. You can change this default by adding the `@DevMCPEnableByDefault` annotation on the method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "You must register the JSON‑RPC service in the deployment module:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Produce a `JsonRPCProvidersBuildItem`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Specify the class in your runtime or runtime‑dev module that contains the methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"`@JsonRpcDescription` is mandatory for Dev MCP; without it the method is only available in the Dev UI.\n"
"The method can return primitives, `String`, `JsonObject`, `JsonArray`, or any POJO that can be serialised to JSON.\n"
"Asynchronous methods (`Uni`, `CompletionStage` or methods annotated with `@NonBlocking`) are also supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "MCP Tools against the Deployment classpath"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Sometimes you need to run xref:dev-ui.adoc#jsonrpc-against-the-deployment-classpath[actions on the deployment classpath] (for example, writing configuration files). In that case you do not create a JSON‑RPC service; instead you provide a supplier via a `BuildTimeActionBuildItem`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The code in the `function` runs on the deployment classpath. The function can return a plain value, a `CompletionStage` or `CompletableFuture` for asynchronous work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "By default this tool will be disabled, and the user has to enable it in Dev UI. You can change this default by adding `.enableMcpFunctionByDefault()` in the builder method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "MCP resources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "A resource is data exposed by your extension. There are two ways to create a resource."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "MCP Resources against build time data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Build‑time data that is already exposed to the xref:dev-ui.adoc#optional-build-time-data[Dev UI] can also be made available to Dev MCP. Provide a description when calling `addBuildTimeData()`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "The extra `description` argument is new: without it the data only appears in the Dev UI. Once supplied, the `jokes` data becomes an MCP resource, however, by default this resource will be disabled. You can change the default by passing in `true` as another parameter after description, that will change this default to be enabled. Users can change this in Dev UI anyway, so this is just a sensible default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "MCP Resources against a recorded value"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "To expose recorded values (data produced at runtime by a recorder) as an MCP resource, define a xref:dev-ui.adoc#jsonrpc-against-a-recorded-value[build‑time action] in the deployment module. The action must include a description:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Return or produce a `BuildTimeActionBuildItem`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Use the builder to configure the action."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Set a human‑readable description."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "Provide the runtime value returned by your recorder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "By default this resource will be disabled, and the user has to enable it in Dev UI. You can change this default by adding `.enableMcpFunctionByDefault()` in the builder method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid "JSON‑RPC usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/dev-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"By default all JSON‑RPC methods are visible in the Dev UI. Only methods with descriptions are exposed via Dev MCP.\n"
"You can override this behaviour with the `@JsonRpcUsage` annotation. Pass one or both of the `Usage` enums (`DEV_UI`, `DEV_MCP`) to control where a method is exposed."
msgstr ""
